Add Environment component for conditional rendering based on hosting environment

## Description

Adds a built-in `Environment` component similar to the MVC environment tag helper. Currently, Blazor developers must inject `IHostEnvironment` or `IWebAssemblyHostEnvironment` and write conditional logic manually‚Äîwhich is error-prone for components that run on both Server and WebAssembly.

### Changes

- **New `Environment` component** (`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Environment`)
  - `Include`: comma-separated environments to render in
  - `Exclude`: comma-separated environments to suppress rendering (takes precedence)
  - Case-insensitive matching, follows tag helper semantics

- **WebAssembly support**
  - Added `WebAssemblyHostEnvironmentAdapter` implementing `IHostEnvironment`
  - Registered automatically in WebAssembly DI container
  - Added `Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting.Abstractions` reference

- **Namespace conflict resolution**
  - Updated existing `Environment.NewLine` usages to `System.Environment.NewLine` in affected files

### Usage

```razor
<Environment Include="Development">
    <div class="alert">Debug mode enabled</div>
</Environment>

<Environment Include="Development, Staging">
    <p>Pre-production environment</p>
</Environment>

<Environment Exclude="Production">
    <p>@DateTime.Now</p>
</Environment>
```

