# Summary
Proposal addressing https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/6818 by introducing a reusable `BasePath` component that centralizes how Blazor apps compute their `<base>` URI when hosted under subpaths.

# Background
Apps mounted at `/dashboard` rely on manually editing `<base href>` or injecting JavaScript to keep casing in sync, which was brittle and inconsistent across Server, Auto, and standalone WebAssembly hosts. `BasePath` standardizes this by:
- Automatically mirroring `HttpContext.Request.PathBase` casing for Blazor Web / hybrid scenarios.
- Providing `Href` and `FallbackHref` parameters for environments (like static WASM hosting) where `PathBase` isn‚Äôt available.
- Normalizing URLs (trailing slash, absolute URI handling) to avoid resource lookup failures in deeper folder structures.

This gives developers a first-class, framework-supported answer instead of per-app workarounds mentioned throughout #6818.

# Changes

## New public API
```
namespace Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web;

/// <summary>
/// Renders a &lt;base&gt; element whose href aligns with the current request's base path.
/// </summary>
public sealed class BasePath : ComponentBase
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Gets or sets an explicit base path to render. When provided, this value takes precedence
    /// over values inferred from the current request or fallback parameters.
    /// </summary>
    /// <example>
    /// <code>
    /// &lt;BasePath Href="/dashboard/" /&gt;
    /// </code>
    /// </example>
    [Parameter]
    public string? Href { get; set; }

    /// <summary>
    /// Gets or sets the fallback href to use when the current request information isn't available.
    /// </summary>
    /// <example>
    /// <code>
    /// &lt;BasePath FallbackHref="/dashboard/" /&gt;
    /// </code>
    /// </example>
    [Parameter]
    public string? FallbackHref { get; set; }
}
```

## Implementation Details
- `BasePath` renders a `<base>` element, defaulting to `HttpContext.Request.PathBase` when available.
- Supports overrides (`Href`) and static fallbacks (`FallbackHref`) while running normalization (leading slash, trailing slash, absolute URI path extraction).
- Added unit tests covering PathBase detection, fallback behavior, precedence, and normalization (relative, absolute, multi-segment cases).

## Tests

The component is covered with unit tests and passed manual testing. Adding e2e test seems too heavy for this kind of change.

# API usage
```razor
<!-- Blazor Web layout -->
<head>
    <BasePath />
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>

<!-- Setting explicit base -->
<BasePath Href="/coolapp/" />

<!-- Providing fallback for static hosting -->
<HeadContent>
    <BasePath FallbackHref="/coolapp/" />
</HeadContent>
```

